cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with secrecy outage probability and ergodic secrecy capacity, which are key concepts in information theory. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper focuses on multiuser wireless networks and interference-limited scenarios. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper deals with the performance of a multiuser diversity scheme, which can be seen as a control system. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with wireless communication and transmission of information. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a less likely category, as the paper focuses more on the performance of a multiuser diversity scheme rather than specific cryptographic techniques.
